origin: Hypatia of Alexandria; Egyptian mathematician and philosopher (c. 370-415).
St. Catherine of Alexandria; Greek theologian, philosopher (unkn-c. 307).
Nicole Reine De La Briere; French astronomer (1723-1788).
Catherine Wolfe; American philanthropist, astronomy patron (1816-1900).
Annie Scott Dill Russell; British astronomer (1868-1947); Edward Walter; British astronomer (1851-1928).
Alexander; British doctor, Nobel laureate (1881-1955); Williamina Paton; Scottish-born American astronomer (1857-1911).
Matthew Fontaine; American oceanographer (1806-1873); Antonia Caetana de Paiva Pereira; American astronomer (1866-1952).
Marie (Madame Curie); Polish physicist, chemist, Nobel laureate (1867-1934).
Priscilla Fairfield; American astronomer (1896-1975), Bart Jan; Dutch-American astronomer (1906-1983).
Gerty Theresa Radnitz; Czech-American physiologist; Nobel laureate (1896-1957).
Judith Arlene; member of the Challenger crew (1949-1986).
Sharon Christa Corrigan; civilian school teacher member of the Challenger crew (1948-1986).
Kalpana; American astronaut, Space Shuttle Columbia Mission Specialist (1961-2003).
Alvan; American astronomer (1804-1887); Alvan G.; American astronomer, optician (1832-1897).
Marie; Geologist and oceanographer, created first comprehensive map of the ocean floor and is credited with discovering the Mid-Atlantic Ridge (1920-2006).
Hildegard von Bingen; German writer, composer, mystic and visionary. In Germany she is considered the founder of the scientific study of natural history (1098- 1179).
Annie Jean; American computer scientist, mathematician, and rocket scientist (1933-2011).
E. Margaret; British-American observational astronomer and astrophysicist (1919-2020).
Maryam; Iranian-American mathematician, first female winner of the Fields Medal (1977-2017).
Pasang Lhamu Sherpa; first Nepalese female sherpa to climb Mount Everest (1961-1993).
Marguerite Catherine; French nuclear physicist who discovered the element francium and first woman to be elected to the French Académie des Sciences (1909-1975)).
